href="gr-000G.xml"
addr="gr-000G"
title="Group">Group</fr:link> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a set. Suppose <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> <fr:link
type="local"
href="gr-004Y.xml"
addr="gr-004Y"
title="Left group action">acts</fr:link> on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y\subseteq  X]]></fr:tex>. We say <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> is an <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Invariant Subset</html:dfn> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G\cdot  Y\subseteq  Y]]></fr:tex>, i.e., for each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in  Y]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\in  G]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\cdot  y\in  Y]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>If there is some ambiguity about which group <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> is invariant with respect to, we say <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> is <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex>-Invariant</html:dfn> (or <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Stable under <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex></html:dfn> or <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex>-Stable</html:dfn>).</fr:p>
 
   
